properties.name: zip_code
properties.description: Home zip code of subscriber (customers can choose to manually enter zip at kiosk however data is unreliable)

properties.name: subscriber_type
properties.description: Subscriber = annual or 30-day member; Customer = 24-hour or 3-day member

properties.name: call_number
properties.description: A unique 9-digit number assigned by the 911 Dispatch Center (DEM) to this call. These number are used for both Police and Fire calls.

properties.name: unit_id
properties.description: Unit Identifier. For example E01 for Engine 1 or T01 for Truck 1.

properties.name: incident_number
properties.description: A unique 8-digit number assigned by DEM to this Fire incident.

properties.name: call_type
properties.description: Type of call the incident falls into. See the list below.

properties.name: call_date
properties.description: Date the call is received at the 911 Dispatch Center. Used for reporting purposes.

properties.name: watch_date
properties.description: Watch date when the call is received. Watch date starts at 0800 each morning and ends at 0800 the next day.

properties.name: received_timestamp
properties.description: Date and time of call is received at the 911 Dispatch Center.

properties.name: entry_timestamp
properties.description: Date and time the 911 operator submits the entry of the initical call information into the CAD system

properties.name: dispatch_timestamp
properties.description: Date and time the 911 operator dispatches this unit to the call.

properties.name: response_timestamp
properties.description: Date and time this unit acknowledges the dispatch and records that the unit is en route to the location of the call.

properties.name: on_scene_timestamp
properties.description: Date and time the unit records arriving to the location of the incident

properties.name: transport_timestamp
properties.description: If this unit is an ambulance, date and time the unit begins the transport unit arrives to hospital

properties.name: hospital_timestamp
properties.description: If this unit is an ambulance, date and time the unit arrives to the hospital.

properties.name: call_final_disposition
properties.description: Disposition of the call (Code). For example TH2: Transport to Hospital - Code 2, FIR: Resolved by Fire Department

properties.name: available_timestamp
properties.description: Date and time this unit is not longer assigned to this call and it is available for another dispatch.

properties.name: address
properties.description: Address of midblock point associated with incident (obfuscated address to protect caller privacy)

properties.name: city
properties.description: City of incident

properties.name: zipcode_of_incident
properties.description: Zipcode of incident

properties.name: battalion
properties.description: Emergency Response District (There are 9 Fire Emergency Response Districts)

properties.name: station_area
properties.description: Fire Station First Response Area associated with the address of the incident

properties.name: box
properties.description: Fire box associated with the address of the incident. A box is the smallest area used to divide the City. Each box is associated with a unique unit dispatch order. The City is divided into more than 2,400 boxes.

properties.name: original_priority
properties.description: Initial call priority (Code 2: Non-Emergency or Code 3:Emergency).

properties.name: priority
properties.description: Call priority (Code 2: Non-Emergency or Code 3:Emergency).

properties.name: final_priority
properties.description: Final call priority (Code 2: Non-Emergency or Code 3:Emergency).

properties.name: als_unit
properties.description: Does this unit includes ALS (Advance Life Support) resources? Is there a paramedic in this unit?

properties.name: call_type_group
properties.description: Call types are divided into four main groups: Fire, Alarm, Potential Life Threatening and Non Life Threatening.

properties.name: number_of_alarms
properties.description: Number of alarms associated with the incident. This is a number between 1 and 5.

properties.name: unit_type
properties.description: Unit type

properties.name: unit_sequence_in_call_dispatch
properties.description: A number that indicates the order this unit was assigned to this call

properties.name: fire_prevention_district
properties.description: Bureau of Fire Prevention District associated with this address

properties.name: supervisor_district
properties.description: Supervisor District associated with this address

properties.name: neighborhood_district
properties.description: Neighborhood District associated with this address, boundaries available here: https://data.sfgov.org/d/p5b7-5n3h

properties.name: location
properties.description: Latitude and longitude of address obfuscated either to the midblock, intersection or call box

properties.name: row_id
properties.description: Unique identifier used for managing data updates. It is the concatenation of Call Number and Unit ID separated by a dash

properties.name: latitude
properties.description: Latitude of the address

properties.name: longitude
properties.description: Longitude of the address
